# ================================================
# POSTPER Examples - Environment Variables
# ================================================
#
# To use environment variables:
# 
# 1. Create a .env file in your workspace root:
#
#    BASE_URL=https://httpbin.org
#    API_KEY=demo-api-key-12345
#    USER_ID=123
#    VERSION=v1
#    USERNAME=testuser
#
# 2. Variables are resolved automatically
# 3. Use {{VARIABLE_NAME}} syntax
#
# ================================================

### Use environment variables in URL
GET {{BASE_URL}}/get?user_id={{USER_ID}}&version={{VERSION}}

###

### Use variables in headers
GET {{BASE_URL}}/headers
Authorization: Bearer {{API_KEY}}
Accept: application/json
X-User-ID: {{USER_ID}}

###

### Use variables in body
POST {{BASE_URL}}/post
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{API_KEY}}

{
  "api_key": "{{API_KEY}}",
  "endpoint": "{{BASE_URL}}",
  "user_id": "{{USER_ID}}",
  "username": "{{USERNAME}}"
}

###

### Multiple variables in single request
POST {{BASE_URL}}/anything
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{API_KEY}}
X-User: {{USERNAME}}

{
  "user": {
    "id": "{{USER_ID}}",
    "name": "{{USERNAME}}"
  },
  "version": "{{VERSION}}"
}

###

# ================================================
# Multiple Environment Files
# ================================================
#
# You can create multiple environment files:
#
# .env              - Default (localhost)
# .env.development  - Development server
# .env.production   - Production server
# .env.test         - Test server
#
# The extension automatically loads the appropriate one
# ================================================

### Example using BASE_URL variable
GET {{BASE_URL}}/status

###

### Test with httpbin's /anything endpoint (accepts any path)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/anything/{{VERSION}}/users/{{USER_ID}}

###

### Nested variables work too!
# If you have:
# PROTOCOL=https
# HOST=httpbin.org
# BASE_URL={{PROTOCOL}}://{{HOST}}
GET {{BASE_URL}}/get?test=nested

###

### Variables in query parameters
GET {{BASE_URL}}/get?api_key={{API_KEY}}&user={{USERNAME}}&id={{USER_ID}}